andré malraux dso (french: [ɑ̃dʁe malʁo]; 3 november 1901 – 23 november 1976) was a french novelist, art theorist and minister of cultural affairs. malraux's novel la condition humaine (man's fate) (1933) won the prix goncourt. he was appointed by president charles de gaulle as minister of information (1945–1946) and subsequently as france's first minister of cultural affairs during de gaulle's presidency (1959–1969).